description:
Overview:

The Delivery Driver / Warehouse team member drives over an established route(s) to deliver products and/or picks up returned merchandise from customers. Additionally, this position fulfills all shipping and receiving functions within the Branch.  

Our team member’s value proposition includes competitive compensation and benefits, career path development and a supportive work environment that encourages innovation, creativity, and personal growth. WORLDPAC is proud to offer all our team members a workplace that is both challenging and rewarding, with a commitment to enable each of them to achieve their full potential.



Benefits:* Annual performance review/yearly merit increases
* Opportunities to build a rewarding career with the fastest growing and most innovative replacement parts distributor in the industry
* Extended health care, dental, vision, life insurance, disability
* RRSP match
* Employee assistance program
* Paid time off
* Employee discount


Responsibilities:
* Under general supervision this position drives the Company truck or automobile over an established route(s) to deliver products and/or picks up returned merchandise;
* The candidate will also be responsible for collecting customer accounts and making approved pickups or deliveries;
* Additionally, this position fulfills shipping and receiving functions within the warehouse \\-sorts, organizes and prepares merchandise from receiving or the production areas to storage or to other designated areas, by part and quantity;
* May use computer to enter, maintain, locate and create records, dispatch, confirm customer or stock orders and to generate delivery manifests and receiving documents;
* Follows all safety rules and applicable laws


Qualifications:
* Minimum 3 years’ class G driving experience required;
* Must maintain a clean driver's abstract and immediately notify management of any change in its status;
* Must be able to lift 50 lbs;
* Maintains a professional appearance and follows the customer service philosophy of the Company;
* Must be available Monday to Friday as well as alternating Saturdays


Pay Range: CAD $18\\.50 \\- CAD $18\\.50 /Hr. Location Type: On\\-Site
